In a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Sarah Sanders discussed various topics including the administration's efforts to reduce regulations, the tax bill, the resignation of Omarosa Manigault, the FCC's decision on net neutrality, and the President's response to the Sandy Hook massacre. Sanders also mentioned the President's call with Rupert Murdoch regarding the Disney deal to buy 21st Century Fox, and his commitment to protecting American citizens and addressing the opioid epidemic.